Ahmet Davutolu is a prominent figure in Turkish politics, and he has also held academic and government positions in the past. Between the years 2009 and 2014, he was President Recep Tayyip Erdogan's Minister of Foreign Affairs, and between 2014 and 2016, he was Turkey's Prime Minister. He served as Prime Minister from 2014 to 2016. In addition, he served as a member of parliament in the past and was one of the original members of the Justice and Development Party (AKP). 